RONALD CLARK I BELIEVE IS HIS NAME THOUGHT THAT HE WAS WEALTHY BECAUSE HE HAD MORE BOOKS THAN ANY OF THE STUDENTS THAT HE KNEW.
WHAT HE DIDN'T REALIZE UNTIL LATER WAS THAT HE LIVED IN THE LIBRARY.
HIS FATHER WAS A CUSTODIAN FOR THE LIBRARY.
THE YOUNG BOY DISTANCED HIMSELF FROM HIS PEERS BECAUSE HE WAS EMBARRASSED THAT HE WAS POOR.
HE FELT DIFFERENT THAN THE OTHERS.
HE FOUND WEALTH AMONGST THE BOOKS BECAUSE ANYTIME HE HAD CURIOSITY OR NEEDED KNOWLEDGE HE COULD JUST GRAB A BOOK AND READ UNTIL 3 IN THE MORNING.
WHEN THE LIBRARY WAS CLOSED HE HAD THE FREEDOM TO RUN AROUND IN PLAY.
WHEN HE GOT OLDER, BECAUSE HE HAD HIS FIRST DIP IN LEARNING AND HIS CURIOSITY GREW, HE BECAME THE FIRST IN HIS FAMILY TO GO TO COLLEGE AND GRADUATE WITH A DEGREE.
HE BECAME A PROFESSOR OF A COLLEGE.
HE BROUGHT HIS FATHER WITH HIM TO WORK ONE DAY TO SHOW HIM HIS NAME PLATE.
EVEN THOUGH HE SAID NOTHING, HE KNEW HIS FATHER WAS PROUD BECAUSE HIS FATHER WANTED HIS SON TO HAVE A BETTER LIFE THAN HE HAD.
EVEN THOUGH HE GREW UP POOR HE FELT RICH BECAUSE HIS WEALTH CAME FROM THE GREATEST INVESTMENT OF ALL AND THAT IS HIMSELF.
IN THE 1940S RONALD WAS A POOR BOY WHO LIVED IN THE LIBRARY WITH HIS MOTHER AND FATHER.
HIS FATHER WAS PROMOTED TO LIBRARY CUSTODIAN AND WAXED THE TOPS OF THE LIBRARY CASES WHICH YOU COULD SEE FROM ABOVE ON THE LIBRARY LADDER.
RONALD'S FAVORITE THING TO DO WAS READ WHICH HE DID ALL THE WAY UNTIL 3 AM IN THE MORNING.
HE DIDN'T INVITE HIS PEERS OVER BECAUSE HE WAS EMBARRASSED THAT HE LIVED IN THE LIBRARY AND FELT DIFFERENT FROM THE OTHER KIDS.
HIS PEERS MADE FUN OF HIM.
HE GREW UP TO BE THE FIRST IN HIS FAMILY TO GRADUATE WITH A DEGREE.
HE BECAME A PROFESSOR AT A COLLEGE AND SHOWED HIS FATHER WHO DIDN'T SAY ANYTHING.
RONALD COULD TELL BY HIS FATHER'S FACE WHAT HE FELT.
HIS FATHER WANTED HIS SON TO HAVE A BETTER LIFE THAN HE EXPERIENCED.
RONALD FOUND WEALTH IN THE KNOWLEDGE THAT HE RECEIVED.
HIS CURIOSITY AND PASSION FOR LEARNING WAS SPARKED IN THE LIBRARY HE LIVED IN.
